<BaseLayout title="Editorial Team | FreelancePricingCalc" description="Meet the editorial team behind FreelancePricingCalc — experienced independent contractors and tax professionals who ensure accuracy.">
  <h1>Editorial Team</h1>
  <p>FreelancePricingCalc is developed and maintained by professionals with direct, long-term experience as independent contractors and freelance business advisors. All content is reviewed before publication and updated when tax rates, market benchmarks, or industry standards change.</p>

  <h2>Editor-in-Chief</h2>
  <h3>Phoenix Reyes (PR) — Independent Contractor (10+ years), Freelance Pricing Lead</h3>
  <p>Phoenix Reyes has worked as a full-time independent contractor for more than ten years, building and operating a multi-discipline freelance practice across content strategy, digital marketing, and creative direction. In that time, Phoenix has gone through every phase of the freelance pricing journey — starting out underpriced and overworked, learning the hard lessons about self-employment taxes and overhead costs, rebuilding their rate structure from the ground up using the kind of backward-calculation methodology that drives this site, and eventually raising rates significantly while actually reducing working hours. Phoenix brings that lived experience to every page of FreelancePricingCalc — not abstract theory, but the practical calculations that determine whether a freelance business is financially sustainable or a slow drain. Beyond their own practice, Phoenix has mentored dozens of new freelancers on rate-setting and pricing strategy, and has a deep understanding of the psychological barriers — imposter syndrome, fear of client rejection, undervaluing specialized expertise — that cause freelancers to underprice themselves. At FreelancePricingCalc, Phoenix leads all methodology and content decisions, reviews every guide and FAQ, and ensures the site reflects the realities of freelance business in today's market.</p>

  <h2>Contributing Expert</h2>
  <h3>Wren Atwood (WA) — Enrolled Agent (EA)</h3>
  <p>Wren Atwood is an Enrolled Agent — a federally licensed tax practitioner authorized to represent taxpayers before the IRS — with a practice focused on self-employed individuals and small business owners. Wren has helped hundreds of freelancers and independent contractors understand and manage the tax implications of self-employment: quarterly estimated taxes, self-employment tax, qualified business income (QBI) deductions, retirement plan contributions, and home office deductions. Wren's practical experience with how self-employment taxes actually work — and how profoundly most new freelancers underestimate them — is the foundation of the tax component of FreelancePricingCalc's calculations. At FreelancePricingCalc, Wren reviews all tax-related content, ensures that the self-employment tax treatment in our calculator is accurate and current, and contributes to the tax comparison guides that help freelancers understand the true cost of self-employment versus employee status.</p>

  <h2>Editorial Standards</h2>
  <p>All content on FreelancePricingCalc is reviewed against primary sources — IRS publications, BLS wage and benefits data, and published freelance industry surveys. We do not accept sponsored content from platforms, marketplaces, or service providers. Tax rates and thresholds are updated annually following IRS announcements. FreelancePricingCalc is an informational resource only. Nothing on this site constitutes legal, financial, or tax advice; consult a qualified professional for your specific situation.</p>
